main event: A series of photographs documenting an unidentified flying object (UFO) referred to as 'Gray Goose' taken in Glen Burnie, Maryland in 1949.
interesting points: The photographs include various views of a disc-like object and an aircraft fuselage, Multiple photographs depict the interior and exterior components of the object, Some images show the object displaying mechanical features such as struts or ribs, There is mention of a tripod mounting and brake drum related to the disc, The report is classified as 'UNCLASSIFIED' and 'CONFIDENTIAL'.
